    "created_at": "2015-09-09T21:32:54Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-09T21:32:54Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Another idea could be to force the explosion to the same altitude as the target, but that may have other unwanted side effects.\n\nI'm uncomfortable with that approach, and it would presumably make implementing Airburst in #8717 harder.\n\n> Note that that would require a bigger rework than this, so may be a longer term prospect.\n\nCould we compromise on accepting this hack as temporary fix for Next+1 (maybe minus the yaml exposing so we won't need an upgrade rule later, but instead a TODO explaining the issue and pointing at the proper fix)? The issue is annoying enough in TS and TDX (and #8717) that I'd like to see a quick fix, but I'm not sure I'll have the time for that bigger rework in the next weeks.\n\nFor what it's worth, I did test this and it works well in practice. A mere 2 world units margin doesn't make a difference in any other situation than this. Bullets explode at the right altitude anyway, and air targets fly much higher than 2 or 3 world units above ground so it can't regress AA missiles either. This hack shouldn't cause any regressions and would be easy to replace/revert later.\n"
  },
