    "created_at": "2015-09-21T02:38:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-21T02:38:39Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Can we unhardcode this and put it in the weapon/projectile/warhead/whatever info?\n\nOriginally I actually did that, but this is supposed to be a temporary fix. As @pchote mentioned above, the proper fix would be to base the explosion type on the altitude of the target, rather than the projectile, but I don't feel like adressing that in the next weeks (at least not in time for the feature-freeze).\n\nBut if I unhardcode it now, we'll need another upgrade rule when that proper fix happens, something I'd like to avoid. Exposing this to yaml in the upcoming release and then removing it again in Next+1 in favor of something else would just cause unnecessary headaches.\n"
  },
